Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of characters that need to be appended to string s so that t becomes a subsequence of s. We can solve this problem using a hash set to store the characters of t and then iterating through s backwards. If a character from s is not present in the hash set, we append it to s and break the loop. This approach has a time complexity of O(n) and space complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the strings s and t.

